== 延伸閱讀 ==
* Cash, Wilbur J. ''The Mind of the South'' (1941), 
* {{cite book | author=Richard N. Current, et. al | title= American History: A Survey 7th ed. | url=https://archive.org/details/essentialsofamer00curr | location= New York | publisher= Alfred A. Knopf | year=1987 | id= ISBN 978-0-394-31549-2}}
* Flynt, J. Wayne ''Dixie's Forgotten People: The South's Poor Whites'' (1979). deals with 20th century. 
* {{cite book | author=David M. Katzman | chapter=Black Migration | title= The Reader's Companion to American History | publisher= Houghton Mifflin Company}} 
* {{cite journal|author=James Grossman |title=Chicago and the 'Great Migration' |journal=Illinois History Teacher |volume=3 |issue=2 |year=1996 |url=http://www.lib.niu.edu/ipo/1996/iht329633.html |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060903120830/http://www.lib.niu.edu/ipo/1996/iht329633.html |archivedate=2006-09-03 }}
* Grady McWhiney. ''In Cracker Culture: Celtic Ways in the Old South'' (1988)
* Mary Odem "[https://web.archive.org/web/20070824033625/http://www.southernspaces.org/contents/2007/sanchez/1a.htm Global Lives, Local Struggles: Latin American Immigrants in Atlanta'"] ''Southern Spaces'' 2006  
* {{cite book | author=John O. Allen and Clayton E. Jewett | title=Slavery in the South: A State-by-State History | url=https://archive.org/details/slaveryinsouthst0000jewe | publisher=Greenwood Press | year= 2004 | id=ISBN 978-0-313-32019-4}}
*{{cite book| author=Rayford Logan | title=The Betrayal of the Negro from Rutherford B. Hayes to Woodrow Wilson | location= New York | publisher=Da Capo Press | year=1997 | id=ISBN 978-0-306-80758-9}}
*  {{cite book | author=William B. Hesseltine | title=A History of the South, 1607-1936 | url=https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.153241 | publisher= Prentice-Hall | year=1936}}
* George Sanchez "[https://web.archive.org/web/20070824033625/http://www.southernspaces.org/contents/2007/sanchez/1a.htm Latinos, the American South, and the Future of U.S. Race Relations]" ''Southern Spaces'' 2007
* {{cite book | editor=Robert W. Twyman. and David C. Roller, ed. | title=Encyclopedia of Southern History | publisher= LSU Press | year= 1979 |ISBN = 0-8071-0575-9}}
* Winders, Jamie. "[https://web.archive.org/web/20070927213205/http://southernspaces.org/contents/2004/global_context/1a.htm Latino Migration and Nashville, Tennessee,]" ''Southern Spaces'' 2004.
* {{cite book | editor=Charles Reagan Wilson and William Ferris, ed. | title=Encyclopedia of Southern Culture | url=https://archive.org/details/encyclopediaofso00dia_teb | publisher= University of North Carolina Press | year= 1989 |ISBN = 0-8078-1823-2}}
